</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<p><span style=3D"text-decoration: underline;"><span style=3D"text-decorati=
on: underline;"><strong>Things to Remember:</strong></span></span></p>
<p>=E2=97=8F&nbsp;OBP is considered more accurate than Batting Average in m=
easuring a player=E2=80=99s offensive value, since it takes into account hi=
ts <em>and</em> walks. A player could bat over .300, but if they don=E2=80=
=99t walk at all, they=E2=80=99re not helping their team as much as a .270 =
hitter with a .380 OBP.</p>
<p>=E2=97=8F&nbsp;A player=E2=80=99s OBP is a good predictor of their<em> f=
uture</em> OBP after 500 plate appearances. So if Pujols has a .500 OBP aft=
er only 50 plate appearances, don=E2=80=99t expect him to continue reaching=
 base at that rate.</p>
<p>=E2=97=8F OBP treats every type of hit and walk equally, meaning that a =
player who goes 2-4 with two singles will have a .500 OBP but a players who=
 goes 1-4 with a home run will have a .250 OBP.</p>
